  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Orthopedic tibial tray primary stability credibility assessment (MRL 3)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a finite element model predicting primary stability (micromotion) of a cementless tibial tray under physiological loading conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can predict relative micromotion patterns across three implant-bone interface configurations at Model Risk Level 3. All 13 credibility factors are fully assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 3. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is applied to bone material property inputs. Decision: Accepted.",
