      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/discretization-mrl3-tibial",
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study across three densities with Richardson extrapolation. Grid convergence index for peak micromotion QoI is 2.1%, well below the 5% threshold. Spatial and temporal discretization errors are quantified and reported. Achieved level 3 exceeds requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-mrl3-tibial",
      "rationale": "Cadaveric test conditions documented including specimen preparation protocol, loading fixture alignment, temperature, and strain gauge calibration records. ISO 14243-1 loading waveforms applied in both simulation and physical test. Environmental conditions (temperature 37°C, hydrated bone) replicated in FE boundary conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-mrl3-tibial",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison metrics defined a priori: mean absolute error, 95th percentile error, and Pearson correlation coefficient between FE-predicted and experimentally measured micromotion at 12 interface locations. MAE of 8.3 µm (gait) and 11.1 µm (stair) against experimental standard deviation of 14.2 µm and 16.8 µm respectively. Correlation r > 0.91 for both loading cases."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl3-tibial",
      "rationale": "Peak interface micromotion (µm) is the primary QoI and is directly linked to the clinical threshold for osseointegration failure (>150 µm per Pilliar et al.). The QoI is identical between the validation experiments and the COU prediction target, ensuring direct relevance without surrogate mapping."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl3-tibial",
      "rationale": "Validation activities used the same tibial tray geometry, implant material (Ti-6Al-4V), and bone preparation conditions as the COU. Loading profiles match ISO 14243-1 as specified in the COU. Cadaveric bone density range (0.18–0.42 g/cm³) spans the patient population envelope identified in the COU requirement document."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-mrl3-tibial",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver convergence tolerance set to 1e-8 for displacement and contact force residuals. Newton-Raphson iteration count and residual histories logged for all production runs. No unconverged increments detected across all 15 production simulations. Solver error contribution to total QoI uncertainty estimated at <0.5% via sensitivity analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-mrl3-tibial",
      "rationale": "Model setup procedure documented in a controlled simulation plan reviewed by a second analyst. Input deck peer review checklist completed with sign-off. Boundary condition and material assignment verified against CAD and material database by an independent reviewer. No use errors identified during review; one minor unit inconsistency corrected prior to production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-mrl3-tibial",
      "rationale": "Continuum FE formulation with isotropic linear elastic bone material and frictional contact (µ = 0.4) is consistent with the literature consensus for primary stability prediction at MRL 3. Model form assumptions documented and justified: cortical shell modeled explicitly; cancellous bone assigned density-modulus relationship from Morgan et al. (2003). Sensitivity of QoI to model form choices quantified via alternative material law comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-mrl3-tibial",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed on bone elastic modulus (log-normal distribution, CV = 22%) and apparent density (CV = 18%) using 500 Latin hypercube samples. 95th percentile prediction interval for peak micromotion reported. Implant geometry inputs derived from certified CMM measurements of production components. Loading input uncertainty from ISO 14243-1 force tolerances incorporated. Achieved level 3 exceeds requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-mrl3-tibial",
      "rationale": "Six cadaveric tibiae from donors aged 62–74 years (4 male, 2 female) with bone mineral density T-scores between −1.0 and +0.5, representing the target patient population. Sample size justified by power analysis targeting 80% power to detect 20 µm difference in peak micromotion. Specimen provenance, storage, and preparation documented per ASTM F2450."
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/input-equivalency-mrl3-tibial",
      "rationale": "Systematic comparison of input parameters between validation experiments and COU performed using a parameter equivalency matrix. Bone density distributions, implant geometry tolerances, interface friction coefficients, and loading magnitudes all confirmed equivalent within specified tolerances. Documented deviations: cadaveric specimens used fresh-frozen rather than fresh; sensitivity analysis confirms <3% effect on peak micromotion QoI."
    }
